---
---

<section id="operations" class="section-surface">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Operations</p>
      <h2>We handle more than the link.</h2>
      <p>
        The work can include rollout, billing, access management, monitoring, and support,
        depending on how the site needs to run.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="focus-grid">
      <article class="card focus-card">
        <p class="focus-index">01</p>
        <h3>Hospitals and clinics</h3>
        <p>Reliable connectivity for clinical work, reporting, staff coordination, and core facility operations.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card focus-card">
        <p class="focus-index">02</p>
        <h3>Businesses and institutions</h3>
        <p>Satellite-backed service, branch connectivity, billing workflows, and managed operations support.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card focus-card">
        <p class="focus-index">03</p>
        <h3>Remote and community sites</h3>
        <p>Deployments in underserved areas where the internet stack needs to be practical and self-sustaining.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="approach-grid">
      <div class="card approach-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">What we handle</p>
        <h3>The operating layer can sit with us.</h3>
        <ul class="approach-list">
          <li>Site review and connectivity planning</li>
          <li>Satellite equipment and edge placement</li>
          <li>Internal distribution across the site</li>
          <li>Billing, access workflows, and monitoring</li>
          <li>Practical support and continuity planning</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="approach-visual card" aria-label="CloudBridge operating model">
        <div class="approach-visual-header">
          <p class="eyebrow">Operating layer</p>
          <h3>Planning, service control, and support stay connected to the network.</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="approach-stage-grid">
          <article class="approach-stage">
            <div class="approach-stage-top">
              <p class="approach-stage-index">01</p>
              <p class="approach-stage-label">Planning layer</p>
            </div>
            <h3>Plan the site</h3>
            <p>Review location, size the link, map coverage, and place equipment before deployment.</p>
            <div class="approach-stage-rows">
              <div>
                <span>Includes</span>
                <strong>Link sizing and coverage map</strong>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span>Sets up</span>
                <strong>Deployment decisions</strong>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="approach-stage">
            <div class="approach-stage-top">
              <p class="approach-stage-index">02</p>
              <p class="approach-stage-label">Service layer</p>
            </div>
            <h3>Run the service</h3>
            <p>Handle billing, access rules, accounts, and daily workflows as part of the operating stack.</p>
            <div class="approach-stage-rows">
              <div>
                <span>Handles</span>
                <strong>Accounts and access rules</strong>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span>Keeps</span>
                <strong>Billing tied to live usage</strong>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="approach-stage">
            <div class="approach-stage-top">
              <p class="approach-stage-index">03</p>
              <p class="approach-stage-label">Continuity layer</p>
            </div>
            <h3>Keep it reliable</h3>
            <p>Monitor the site, respond to issues, and support continuity once the network is live.</p>
            <div class="approach-stage-rows">
              <div>
                <span>Tracks</span>
                <strong>Service health and issues</strong>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span>Protects</span>
                <strong>Day-to-day uptime</strong>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>

        <p class="approach-summary">
          The network stays usable because the operating layer does not get left behind.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .focus-grid,
  .approach-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-16);
  }

  .focus-card,
  .approach-card,
  .approach-visual {
    padding: var(--space-24);
  }

  .focus-card {
    background: var(--color-surface-strong);
  }

  .focus-index,
  .approach-stage-index {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-subtle);
  }

  .focus-card h3,
  .approach-card h3,
  .approach-stage h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .approach-card .eyebrow,
  .approach-visual-header .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .approach-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    margin-top: var(--space-16);
  }

  .approach-visual {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-24);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .approach-visual-header {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .approach-visual-header h3 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
  }

  .approach-stage-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-16);
  }

  .approach-stage {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-16);
    min-height: 224px;
    padding: var(--space-24);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    background: var(--color-surface-strong);
  }

  .approach-stage-top {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .approach-stage-index {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .approach-stage-label {
    color: var(--color-subtle);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .approach-stage-rows {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  .approach-stage-rows div {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .approach-stage-rows span {
    color: var(--color-subtle);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .approach-stage-rows strong {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .approach-summary {
    padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-24);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    background: var(--color-text);
    color: var(--color-surface);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (min-width: 960px) {
    .focus-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .approach-grid {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(320px, 0.8fr) minmax(0, 1.2fr);
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .approach-stage-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .approach-stage-rows div {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: var(--space-16);
    }

    .approach-stage-rows strong {
      max-width: 13rem;
      text-align: right;
    }
  }
</style>
